onedrive
OneDrive is a personal cloud storage service. Each user gets their own OneDrive storage space, which they can use to save personal work files, photos, and documents. 
Users can set permissions to control who can view or edit the shared files.

SharePoint
It is designed for team collaboration, and content sharing within an organization. SharePoint sites can be used to host various types of content, such as documents, lists, and calendars. 
Permissions to files are usually shared through permission groups with multiple onwers, ontributors and viewers.

Microsoft Teams:
Microsoft Teams is a communication and collaboration platform that brings together chat,  file storage, and app integrations into a single hub for teamwork. 
Within Microsoft Teams, users can create channels to organize conversations and share files related to specific topics or projects. 

